HUMAN RIGHTS

## OBJECTIVE:  Respect for human rights

PUBLIC DOCUMENTS:  Eni's Code of Ethics, ECG Policy - Respect for Human Rights in Eni, Eni's management of whistleblowing reports received from Eni SpA and its subsidiaries.

## PRINCIPLES

- ·  Ensure respect for internationally recognized Human Rights in its own activities and those of its commercial partners, in line with the United Nations Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights (UNGP) and with the OECD Guidelines for Multinational Enterprises;
- ·  Carrying out Human Rights Due Diligence in its activities. Assess potential and actual impacts, and improve prevention and mitigation of such impacts;
- ·  Respect rights of people and communities by recognizing and enhancing their culture, lifestyles, institutions, ties with the land of origin and development models in line with international standards;
- ·  Engage Third Parties in the prevention and mitigation of any adverse Human Rights impacts;
- ·  Verifying and providing remedy, including through cooperation with Third Parties, in case of adverse Human Rights impacts it might have caused (or contributed to causing).

SUPPLIERS

OBJECTIVE:  Develop the sustainable supply chain

PUBLIC DOCUMENTS:  Eni's Code of Ethics, Supplier Code of Conduct, ECG Policy - Respect for Human Rights in Eni, Eni's position on Conflict Minerals and Eni's Slavery and Human Trafficking Statement.

## PRINCIPLES

- ·  Adopt accurate qualification, selection and monitoring processes of our suppliers and partners, based on the principles of transparency and integrity, and don't tolerate collusive practices, in full respect of legality;
- ·  Select commercial partners that comply with the Eni Supplier Code of Conduct;
- ·  Promote long-term strategic partnerships based on an integrated, coordinated and transparent approach, encouraging an equitable sharing of risks and opportunities;
- ·  Require suppliers to prohibit all forms of modern slavery, child labour, discrimination or abuse, establish clear and fair working conditions in a safe and healthy working environment and respect the cultural, economic and social rights of the local communities and vulnerable groups;
- ·  Promote communication and awareness-raising among suppliers, requiring them to spread respect for Human Rights across their own supply chains.

TRANSPARENCY, ANTI-CORRUPTION AND TAX STRATEGY

OBJECTIVE:  Fight any form of corruption, with no exception

PUBLIC DOCUMENTS:  'Anti-Corruption' MSG; Eni's management of whistleblowing reports received from Eni SpA and its subsidiaries; Tax Strategy; Eni's position on Contractual Transparency; and Eni's Code of Ethics.

## PRINCIPLES

- ·  Conduct business with loyalty, fairness, transparency, honesty and integrity and in compliance with laws;
- ·  Prohibit without exception all forms of corruption;
- ·  Always ensure compliance with laws, rules and regulations governing the prevention of corruption and money laundering applicable;
- ·  Carry out periodic awareness-raising, communication and training initiatives on anti-corruption and antimoney laundering;
- ·  Guarantee the communication of the Anti Corruption MSG to Third Parties at Risk through specific contractual clauses and/or declarations and promoting training and awareness raising initiatives dedicated to them;
- ·  Ascertain the ethical and reputational reliability of our potential business partners.

LOCAL COMMUNITIES

OBJECTIVE:  Promote relations with local communities and contribute to their sustainable development also through public-private partnerships PUBLIC DOCUMENTS:  Eni's Code of Ethics, ECG Policy - Respect for Human Rights in Eni and; Alaska Indigenous Peoples.

## PRINCIPLES

- ·  Working with communities, development enabler and local organizations to foster autonomous, lasting, and sustainable local growth;
- ·  Consider the environmental, social, health, safety and security aspects and respect for Human Rights in all our activities, since the earliest feasibility assessments, in cooperation with local communities and other relevant stakeholders;
- ·  Promote continuous and transparent consultation in order to inform local communities and other relevant stakeholders and ensure that their expectations are always taken into consideration within our activities;
- ·  Establish strong, lasting relationships and partnerships with the communities in which Eni operates in order to build lasting, shared value;
- ·  Respect the rights of individuals and local communities of the countries where it operates, with particular reference to the highest attainable standard of health.

